  plantName: Tulip
  description: A tulip is a Eurasian herbaceous, bulbiferous perennial plant in the
    genus Tulipa, renowned for its large, showy, cup-shaped spring flowers, often
    in shades of red, pink, yellow, or white. They are popular garden plants, cut
    flowers, and, in some cases, edible, representing a major cultural symbol of
    the Netherlands.
